docs.abstract: The Swiss conglomerate made a surprise $3.4 billion offer nearly three years after Yoox and Net-a-Porter merged in an all-share deal.
docs.snippet: The Swiss conglomerate made a surprise $3.4 billion offer nearly three years after Yoox and Net-a-Porter merged in an all-share deal.
docs.lead_paragraph: Compagnie Financière Richemont built a conglomerate offering the world’s wealthiest consumers the highest-quality product, often in the most luxurious of settings. Clients walking into a Cartier flagship or a Piaget boutique — both Richemont brands — could expect radiant smiles and soft furnishings, as well as impeccable service for as long as was necessary before they made their purchase.

headline.main: Richemont, Doubling Down on Online Luxury, May Buy Yoox Net-a-Porter
headline.print_headline: Swiss Luxury Conglomerate Bets Big on Online Shopping
